# Force LF line endings for ALL text files, on every OS.
#
# Why: On Windows, Git's default `core.autocrlf=true` converts LFŌåÆCRLF on
# checkout and CRLFŌåÆLF on commit. This causes:
#   1. Phantom diffs in worktrees (blocks auto-rebase)
#   2. Broken shell scripts (bash can't parse \r\n shebang)
#   3. Noisy diffs when files round-trip through different OS
#
# `text=auto` lets Git detect binary files (images, fonts, etc.) and leave
# them alone. `eol=lf` forces LF in the working tree for everything else.
# Every modern tool (VS Code, Node, browsers) handles LF on Windows fine.

* text=auto eol=lf
